## Section Guidelines

### Title & Description

- Clear, descriptive title
- One paragraph explaining purpose and value
- Target audience: developers who are new to this component

### Quick Start

- 5 minutes or less to get running
- Copy-paste-able commands
- Include verification step
- Link to detailed setup if more complex

### Features

Table format works well for scanning:
- Feature name in first column
- Brief description in second column
- Keep descriptions concise

### Configuration

- Show example configuration files
- Document all options with defaults
- Group related options together
- Include type information

### Usage Examples

- 2-3 common use cases
- Working code examples
- Comments explaining key parts
- Real-world scenarios

### Troubleshooting

- Top 3-5 most common issues
- Clear problem description
- Step-by-step solutions
- Include commands when applicable

### Related Documentation

- Always link to CLAUDE.md for architecture
- Link to parent README if nested
- Include external resources if helpful

